Hi Tom,

Thanks for putting the link up. H'mm even though my eyesight is pretty
dam bad, I went and had a look at the illustrations, which were very
interesting, but would you or anyone else like to proffer some
interpretations? Apart from the TSUKA (sword grip), YA (arrow) and YUMI
(bow), I was on the whole a bit lost. What the heck was the thing that
looked like a dog kennel next to the JIN MAKU (camp curtain), and the
seemingly miniature TAIKO (drum), a container maybe? And as to the other
stuff...?

Yours curiously

Dean
